What's useful to know about Amazon EC2? EC2 stands for Elastic Compute Cloud. Instance type optimizes compute, memory, storage, or high-performance-computing. User chooses OS, instance type, storage, and networking. Automatically scales to adjust network capacity by demand. Amazon Machine Images simplify deployment. EBS volumes provide EC2 instances persistent storage. Spot instances can dramatically cut server costs. EC2 works seamlessly with other AWS services.
